>> Playwright Download Process:

=> We have to Install nodeJS from the official website of nodeJS.
=> For check the version of nodeJS:
    Open Terminal
    and write: npm --version 
                    or
               npm -v

>> Installation Process:
>> Installing using command as npm package:

STEP 1:
==> Create a new folder and open in VS Code.


STEP 2:
==> Goto Terminal of VS Code and run command:
              npm init playwright@latest

  => If you want to install any specific version so write that version at latest place  
              for eg= playwright@9.6.2 etc.

==> Then, teminal asks you some Qustions like what do you want and all other stuff,
    so give it the answer with which you want to do.

STEP 3:
==> Following will be added:
    ==> package.json           = node project management file
    ==> playwright.json        = Configuration file
    ==> tests folder           = absic example test
    ==> tests-examples folder  = detailed example tests
    ==> .gitignore             = to be used during git commit and push
    ==> playwright.yml         = to be used during CI/CD Pipeline

STEP 4:
==> Check Playwright added:
          npm playwright -v

STEP 5: Check Playwright command options:
          npx playright -h
                  or
          npx playwright --help


















